# MuseDAM React Core Specification

## 1. Directory Structure & Reuse (Aligned with actual project)

- Atomic UI: `src/components/ui/` (Button, Input, Badge, Dialog, etc. – shadcn/radix)
- Business components (reuse first): root-level files such as AssetThumbnail.tsx, ConfirmDialog.tsx, UserAvatar.tsx, UserSelect.tsx, AuthProvider.tsx, PageLoadingFallback.tsx, ThemeProvider.tsx
- Domain/feature folders: approval-center/, dnd/, upload/, AssetTypeIcon/, SimpleTooltip/, etc.
- Icons: `src/components/icons/` (Figma MCP first)
- Workflow: Before creating any new component, check existing files and reuse or place in correct domain folder. Prefer extending variants/props over creating a parallel component. Never reinvent the wheel.
- Page files should orchestrate data and layout only; move complex visual blocks into the correct domain folder.
- If the same visual block or logic appears twice, extract a reusable component, hook, util, mapper, or constants module.
- Avoid wrapper-only components with no design or domain value.

## 2. Layout & Auto Layout

- No fixed width: ban 1440px. Use `w-full`, `max-w-7xl`, `container`.
- Flexbox priority: strictly use `gap` for spacing between siblings. NO MARGIN.
- Spacing scale: multiples of 4 only (4, 8, 12, 16, 20, 24, 32, 40, 48) → Tailwind gap-1 to gap-12.

## 3. Color Tokens (Absolute – 100% from designer guidelines)

- Light: Text `#192038` (basic light 800), secondary `#8F9BB3` (basic light 500). NEVER `#C5CEE0` for text.
- Background: Page `#F7F9FC`, Card `#FFFFFF`.
- Border: `#E4E9F2`.
- Brand: `#3366FF` (hover `#598BFF`, active `#274BDB`).
- Dark: Page `#1F1F1F`, Card/Sidebar `#262626`, Border `#595959`.
- All colors must come from globals.css CSS variables.

## 4. Visual Standards

- Radius: Button/Input 6px, Card 8px, Modal 12px, Tag 4px.
- Shadow: Cards are border-only. Shadows reserved for Dropdowns, Popovers, Modals (use --shadow-dropdown).
- Height: Form controls default to Medium (36px).
- Typography: exactly as in designer guidelines (H5 22/32, H6 20/28, etc.).

## 5. Icons & Emojis

- Functional icons: MUST use `src/components/icons/` (Figma first, lucide-react fallback).
- Decorative emojis: only if Figma layer is TEXT type.
